titleInfo.title: (PC) Young v. Jefferies, et al
titleInfo.subTitle: ORDER signed by Magistrate Judge Edmund F. Brennan on 04/28/15 ORDERING that defendant has complied with the 07/01/14 discovery order; plaintiff's 45 request to amend his discovery motion is GRANTED; plaintiff's amended motion to compel is GRANTED in part and DENIED in part: the request to compel production of the entirety of defendant's personnel records is DENIED; the request to compel production of information bearing on any allegations or discipline of defendant for excessive force is GRANTED; within 21 days, defendant shall either produce relevant documents, including documents from personnel files, concerning any complaints, investigations and disciplinary actions while defendant was employed by CDCR, for alleged conduct that is similar to that alleged in plaintiff's complaint (i.e., excessive force), or provide a properly verified response that no such records exist; the 24 02/04/14 order denying plaintiff's motion for the appointment of counsel is reconsidered and GRANTED, plaintiff's 22 request for the appointment of counsel is GRANTED. Case referred to Sujean Park, the courts pro bono coordinator (cc: Park) (Benson, A)
